- String manipulation
- String comparison
- Extraction of substrings
- Split a string by separator chars.

Each character has a serial number from the Unicode table.

string is an alias of the System.String class.
A string is a sequence of characters stored in a certain address in memory.
A string is an array of characters.
Values of the type string are stored in the dynamic memory(managed heap)
Variables of the type string keep a reference to an object in the heap.

Strings are immutable
After being assigned once, the content of the variable does not change directly.
If we try to change the value, it will be saved to a new location in the dynamic
memory and the variable will point to it.

Creating and Initializing a String
- is a process associated with the allocation of the dynamic memory are (the heap)
